I am writing this to complain about a software company named Verant.  They run a game I play called Everquest.  Everquest is an online roleplaying game, with close to 500,000 customers.<br>
<br>
Everquest is a full screen game (Windows is automatically disabled).  I have no access to my other Microsoft products while this game is being played.  Because of this limitation, someone wrote a program called EQW, which allowed Everquest to be played in a Window.  This program allowed me to have access to my Microsoft programs (MSN chat, Explorer, Word, etc.) while I was playing this game.<br>
<br>
Recently, Verant introduced something that alters the way my windows (and mouse work).   I am no longer able to play the game and have access to Microsoft programs at the same time.<br>
<br>
My questions to you are:<br>
<br>
Is Verant allowed to alter the way that my MS Windows works without Microsoft permission?<br>
<br>
Is Verant allowed to stop my mouse from working in a particular window without Microsoft permission?<br>
<br>
Is Verant allowed to shut down my access to Microsoft products while I play their game?<br>
<br>
Thank you<br>
<br>
